               <history>
                  <origin>On f. 2b it is recorded that the work was finished in Benares/Varanasi in
                     the year 1198 AH, equal to the 27th year of the reign of Shāh ‘Ālam. <origDate
                        calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1784">1198 AH (1784 CE)</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Presented to the Library of East India House by <persName
                           key="person_12414465" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Sir John
                           Malcom</persName>, 19 May 1827.</p>
                     <p>Formerly part of the collection of the Persian scholar <persName
                           type="standard"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/#Bland,_Nathaniel,_1803-1865"
                           key="person_20108923" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Nathaniel
                           Bland (1803-1865)</persName>. Bland’s oriental manuscripts were sold
                        through Bernard Quaritch in 1866 to <persName type="standard"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/#Crawford,_Alexander_Crawford_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1812-1880"
                           key="person_97751058" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Alexander
                           Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford</persName>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Purchased by Enriqueta Rylands, on behalf of the John Rylands Library, in
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from <persName
                           type="standard"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/#Crawford,_James_Ludovic_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1847-1913"
                           key="person_9985420" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">James Ludovic
                           Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford</persName>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
